 whether in affairs of state or affairs of the heart. This beautifully written work crisscrosses Europe, with a special focus on Italy, to explore attitudes toward the art of dissimulation in the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries. Discussing many canonical and lesser-known works, Jon R. Snyder examines the treatment of dissimulation in early modern treatises and writings on the court, civility, moral philosophy, political theory, and in the visual arts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aInterpersonal communicationxHistoryxEurope. 0aInterpersonal communicationxHistoryxItaly. 0aInterpersonal communicationzEuropexHistory. 0aInterpersonal communicationzItalyxHistory. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectsxHistoryxEurope. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectsxHistoryxItaly. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectszEuropexHistory. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspectszItalyxHistory. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectsxHistoryxEurope. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectsxHistoryxItaly. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectszEuropexHistory. 0aTruthfulness and falsehoodxSocial aspectszItalyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944442423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520944442.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles